---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
---

<BaseLayout title="About" description="About Chiaroscuro Joven — who is behind the site and why it exists.">
  <section class="container container--reading">
    <p class="section-label">About</p>
    <h1>Light from darkness</h1>

    <p>
      <em>Chiaroscuro Joven</em> — literally "young chiaroscuro" — is the name I publish under
      when the writing isn't about work or products or companies. It's a place for the things
      that inspire me: paintings I can't stop looking at, books that rearrange something
      inside, films that teach you to see, ideas I'm still turning over.
    </p>

    <p>
      The visual language here is borrowed from the Baroque masters who invented it — Caravaggio,
      Artemisia Gentileschi, Georges de La Tour. Light that doesn't flatter, light that reveals.
      Deep black ground, warm flesh, a candle flame carrying the whole composition.
    </p>

    <p>
      New here, a new corner of the internet. If you landed here somehow: welcome. The gallery
      is still filling. The community space opens soon. The blog starts when it starts.
    </p>

    <p class="sign-off">— Chiaroscuro Joven</p>
  </section>
</BaseLayout>

<style>
  p {
    margin-bottom: 20px;
    font-size: 1.05rem;
  }

  .sign-off {
    margin-top: 48px;
    font-family: var(--cj-serif);
    font-style: italic;
    color: var(--cj-gold);
  }
</style>
